</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="3" pageNumber="98" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1436,151,285]" pageId="3" pageNumber="98">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,334,223,249]" pageId="3" pageNumber="98">Etymology.</emphasis>
The name of the new species is derived from the subapical area of posterior process of male tenth abdominal tergite with 1 spine on inner margin. Latin “ 
<emphasis box="[769,800,259,284]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="98">in-</emphasis>
” means inner margin; Latin “ 
<emphasis box="[1135,1182,259,284]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="98">spin</emphasis>
-” means spine.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
